Ratios of P2 width and plaque shape (P2/w/l/s) ca. 3/4/8/1. P1 laminate; median carina sinuate in profile. P2 raised, l/w ca. 2/1, sides converging toward blunt apex. Plaques very large, very narrowly separated, more narrowly so at posterior than at anterior, weakly raised. Metaventrite anteriorly with very low midlongitudinal ridge. AIS width at straight posterior margin ca. 1.7x P2. All legs moderately long and slender. Profemur (male) without tubercle next to trochanter; protibia very slightly arcuate, gradually increasing in width from base to apex. Meso- and metatibia straight. Abdominal apex symmetrical; last tergite (male) notched. Aedeagus as illustrated (
Fig. 33
). Female tergite X, gonocoxite, and spermatheca as illustrated (
Fig. 390
).
